In this update:
[1] India (Kerala state)
[2] Philippines (Iloilo province)

******
[1] India (Kerala state)
Date: Thu 28 Aug 2014
Source: The New Indian Express [edited]
http://www.newindianexpress.com/cities/kochi/Four-Cases-of-Chikungunya-Confirmed/2014/08/28/article2402329.ece


4 confirmed cases of chikungunya were reported from Calvathy Colony at Fort Kochi [Kochi, Kerala state]. Officials have identified 30 people showing the symptoms of the disease. The colony is inhabited by low-income families. The disease was 1st detected 2 weeks ago [around 14 Aug 2014].

District Medical Officer Dr Hasina Muhammed said that the health department is carrying out an intensive drive to prevent further spread of the disease. "Fogging is being done. Drinking water is being supplied to the area in tankers. But poor hygiene and open water containers are becoming the breeding grounds for mosquitoes which are the carriers of the disease [virus]. Steps will be initiated to destroy the source," she said.

A medical camp was held on Tuesday [26 Aug 2014] in the area. 200 people participated in it, out of which only one person showed symptoms of chikungunya [virus infection], she said.

--
