******
[2] Philippines (Iloilo province)
Date: Thu 28 Aug 2014
Source: GMA News [edited]
http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/376757/news/regions/23-chikungunya-cases-confirmed-in-iloilo


At least 23 cases of chikungunya have been confirmed in Iloilo province by the Iloilo Provincial Health Office, after the Research Institute of Tropical Medicine [RITM] analyzed the blood samples of suspected cases sent to it. The RITM results indicated Oton town had the most confirmed cases with 11, followed by Carles with 7, GMA Iloilo reported. Tigbauan town had 2 confirmed cases while Alimodian, Badiangan and Igbaras towns had one case each. Earlier this month [August 2014], Barangay Jovellar in Igbaras town was placed under a state of calamity after some 200 suspected cases were reported there.

Chikungunya is a disease spread by mosquitoes. Its symptoms include headaches, vomiting, joint pains and rashes.

[Byline: Joel Locsin]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Chikungunya virus is endemic in both India and in the Philippines. ProMED posted a report of a dispersed chikungunya outbreak in Iloilo province on 16 Aug 2014 (see ProMED-mail archive no. 20140817.2698268). That outbreak is continuing.

Although chikungunya virus transmission seems to have been fairly quiet in India this year (2014) so far, 2013 saw multiple outbreaks in a variety of localities. - Mod.TY

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2731901,308, https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2731901,34239.]
